<p class="hidden stagger-2" style="max-width:700px;color:var(--dim);font-size:13px;line-height:1.8;margin-top:24px">Beat detection works by monitoring low-frequency energy. When the energy exceeds a threshold relative to recent average energy, a beat is registered. The threshold determines sensitivity — too low catches non-beat transients; too high misses quieter beats. The hold time prevents one loud event from triggering multiple detections.</p>
